text.description:
Salah Al Din Citadel in the background
#justcairothings #cairoscene #cairostyle

Crazy how it pays back in Memories if you tighten your budget:

Landing in Cairo I found myself in an
ideal situation to collect as many memories as I wanted by just leaving the comfort zone on purpose.

I didn't withdraw as much money at the ATM to just don't care about Taxi's Prices and jump into the very next one. I had to search for cheaper methods. Also I didn't spend money on a sim card. So I had no translator or anything else besides offline maps on my phone that would have reduced the thrill.

Later I even learned how to use Minibuses, kind of group Taxis that follow certain routes. Unbelievable cheap. And in the end I went pretty far south using them and saw a lot of incredible beautiful things.

#visitegypt #travelingthroughtheworld #collectmemories #cairo #egypttravel #egyptphotography

Sailing the Illbruck! Are there any faster boats in the baltic sea?

For sure not in 2002 when this thing won the Volvo #oceanrace coming into Kiel 🥳🤯

Did it again because Instagram reels messed around with me
Thanks @speedsailing.de
(2/3) Travel far enough, you meet yourself. This is a screenshot of a video I made at the beautiful Train Street in Hanoi! Walking along there was really a #lifechangingexperience

(1/3) "Never let your memories be greater than your dreams" - It's now over half a year ago that I was in Vietnam. (btw one of the best experiences in my lifetime) And while I couldn't travel since then, I started thinking about the future here in Germany and Europe... The orchestra of 5G technology, artifical Intelligence, quantum computing, 3D printing, drone deliveries, e-mobility, renewable energy... it's coming. And I am concerned if that Europe can keep up the pase when I think about the fact that the WiFi in a tour bus in Vietnam in the middle of nowhere was as good and maybe more consistent then my WiFi at home in Germany in a city...
Scenic Vietnam. What picture of Vietnam in my Grid do you like the most?

text.description:
Over Taipei City.

This is shot from #elephantmountain, 15min walk away from the #Taipei101 which you see in the background. Massively overfilled tourist spot. But most tourist go on the same rocks to make the same Fotos. The Rock I sit here on top, no one started to climb. And when I did people @sunwang1209 started to photograph me even though the rock was just 2m heigh. #dontgowiththeflow

I gave the photographer my Instagram and the next day I got this Foto 😊

Life changing experience. Before this trip I would have never deared to ask people for the photo or to leave my bag at the floor and climb at the top to then bide people of they can help me putting my backpack up.

What travel changed your life?
Edited with City preset @julian.ziese
#bedifferent #individualtourism
